Hi Frank

Found ten spare minutes to knock out a quick choccie bar demo... <!-- s:-) --><img src="{SMILIES_PATH}/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /><!-- s:-) -->

You need to cut n paste the code below into a text editor and save it as (say) "choccie.asl".  In order for the code to work you also need the version of typelib.qlb [url:1brci8ri]http&#58;//members&#46;aol&#46;com/agbampton/html/typelib&#46;zip[/url:1brci8ri]  from my website.  



[code:1brci8ri]' &quot;Chocolate Machine Demo&quot;
' Created with QDK 3&#46;52 
!include &lt;Typelib&#46;qlb&gt;

define game &lt;Chocolate Machine Demo&gt;
	asl-version &lt;350&gt;
	gametype singleplayer
	start &lt;Cafeteria&gt;
	game author &lt;MaDbRiT &gt;
	game version &lt;&#46;001&gt;
	game copyright &lt;Â© 2004&gt;
	game info &lt;Created with QDK 3&#46;52&#46;&gt;
end define

define synonyms
end define

define room &lt;Cafeteria&gt;
	prefix &lt;the&gt;

	define object &lt;machine&gt;
		alias &lt;chocolate machine&gt;
		alt &lt;vending machine; chocolate machine; machine&gt;
		look &lt;it's a Nestle chocolate machine - your favourite brand&#46;&gt;
		type &lt;TLTobject&gt;
		type &lt;TLTcontainer&gt;
		properties &lt;not takeable; noTake=No chance - It probably weighs 400kilos - and it is bolted to the wall!; listHeader=the dispensing tray at the bottom contains &gt;
	end define

	define object &lt;coin&gt;
		alt &lt;money&gt;
		look &lt;its a 50 pence piece - just enough to buy a bar of chocolate&#46;&gt;
		type &lt;TLTobject&gt;
		type &lt;TLTcontainable&gt;
		action &lt;contained&gt; &#123;
			hide &lt;coin&gt;
			show &lt;chocolate&gt;
			msg &lt;The vending machine gives a 'kerchunk' and dispenses a bar of chocolate&#46;&#46;&#46;&gt;
		&#125;
	end define

	define object &lt;chocolate&gt;
		look &lt;Nestle Nutty-Fruit, your favourite!&gt;
		prefix &lt;a bar of&gt;
		hidden
		type &lt;TLTobject&gt;
		type &lt;TLTcontainable&gt;
		properties &lt;isIn=machine&gt;
	end define

end define

define text &lt;intro&gt;
end define

define text &lt;win&gt;
end define

define text &lt;lose&gt;
end define[/code:1brci8ri]

Make sure that typelib and the saved ASL file are in the same folder and this demo should be runnable - you can also open the ASL in QDK and see how I set it up.

The demo isn't fully "mug-trapped" -  making sure any unexpected input is dealt with properly is down to you <!-- s;-) --><img src="{SMILIES_PATH}/icon_e_wink.gif" alt=";-)" title="Wink" /><!-- s;-) -->

Al (MaDbRiT)

Oh yeah - make sure your text editor doesn't line-wrap the longer lines in the code above - that really screws things up!
